HEADWORD: Bowne
<hw>Bowne</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Boun</er>.]</ety> <def>To make ready; to prepare; to dress.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We will all <qex>bowne</qex> ourselves for the banquet.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

